   <abstract>Larkin Harry Brown was born on April 8, 1866 to John and Mary (White) Brown in Pennsylvania. He married Katherine Ann Gaw (1865-1964) on July 29, 1889 and the couple settled in Massachusetts. Their one child, Clarence Leon Brown, was born on May 10, 1890. In about 1902, the family moved to Knoxville, Tennessee where Larkin Brown worked for Brookside Mills. After Clarence Brown became a prominent film director, Larkin and Katherine followed him to Southern California, where Larkin Brown died on March 11, 1942.</abstract>
